'''Mehmet Zeki Çelik''' ({{IPA|tr|ˈzeci ˈtʃelik}}; born 17 February 1997) is a Turkish professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays for {{Italian football updater|Roma}} club [[AS Roma|Roma]] and the [[Turkey national football team|Turkey national team]]. Mainly a [[right-back]], he can also be deployed as a [[centre-back]] in a [[Formation (association football)#3–4–1–2|back three]].

==Early life==
Çelik was born on 17 February 1997 in [[Yıldırım, Bursa|Yıldırım]], [[Bursa Province]]. He is of [[Kurds in Turkey|Kurdish]] descent.<ref>{{Cite web |title=2026 Dünya Kupası Yolunda Milli Gururlar: Zeki Çelik |url=https://www.aa.com.tr/tr/dunyadan-spor/2026-dunya-kupasi-yolunda-milli-gururlar-zeki-celik/3779471 |access-date=2026-04-02 |website=www.aa.com.tr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=AA |date=2025-12-24 |title=Zeki Çelik, İtalyanların kendisine taktığı lakabı açıkladı: 'Hoşuma gidiyor' |url=https://www.hurriyet.com.tr/sporarena/zeki-celik-italyanlarin-kendisine-taktigi-lakabi-acikladi-hosuma-gidiyor-43064898 |access-date=2026-04-02 |website=www.hurriyet.com.tr |language=tr}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Bursaspor===
Born in [[Bursa]] as the youngest of nine children, Çelik went through the [[Bursaspor]] youth academy and became a professional in 2015. He signed on loan with [[Karacabey Birlikspor]] in 2015.

===İstanbulspor===
In 2016, he joined [[İstanbulspor]]. His good performance with İstanbulspor earned him a call-up to the senior [[Turkey national football team|Turkey national team]] in 2018, despite playing in the [[TFF First League]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=286&ftxtID=28999|title=Mehmet Zeki Çelik: Sağın yeni gözdesi - TamSaha Detay Sayfası TFF|website=www.tff.org|access-date=5 June 2018|archive-date=3 June 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210603043540/https://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=286&ftxtID=28999|url-status=live}}</ref>

===Lille===
On 8 July 2018, Çelik signed with [[Lille OSC|Lille]] in France on a five-year contract.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.losc.fr/actualites-foot-lille/zeki-celik-international-turc-est-lillois|title=Zeki Celik, international turc, est Lillois - Lille LOSC|website=www.losc.fr|access-date=12 August 2018|archive-date=3 June 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210603053827/https://www.losc.fr/actualites-foot-lille/zeki-celik-international-turc-est-lillois|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Transferts : Zeki Celik a signé à Lille |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Transferts-zeki-celik-a-signe-a-lille/920582 |access-date=13 August 2018 |work=L'Équipe |date=8 July 2018 |language=fr |archive-date=2 June 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210602213519/https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Transferts-zeki-celik-a-signe-a-lille/920582 |url-status=live }}</ref> Çelik made his professional debut in a 3–1 [[Ligue 1]] win over [[Stade Rennais F.C.|Stade Rennes]] on 11 August 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2018/08/11/france/ligue-1/lille-olympique-sporting-club-metropole/stade-rennais-fc/2792218/|title=Lille vs. Rennes - 11 August 2018 - Soccerway|website=Soccerway|access-date=13 August 2018|archive-date=3 June 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210603021342/https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2018/08/11/france/ligue-1/lille-olympique-sporting-club-metropole/stade-rennais-fc/2792218/|url-status=live}}</ref>

===Roma===
On 5 July 2022, Çelik’s transfer to Roma from Lille was made official by the [[Serie A]] club, [[A.S. Roma|Roma]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://romapress.net/official-zeki-celik-joins-roma-from-lille/|title=Official: Zeki Çelik joins Roma from Lille - A.S. Roma|website=www.romapress.net |date=5 July 2022 }}</ref> He has signed a four-year contract with the Giallorossi that runs until 30 June 2026.<ref>{{cite news |title=Zeki Celik Completes Move to Roma |url=https://www.asroma.com/en/news/2022/7/zeki-celik-completes-move-to-roma |access-date=5 July 2022 |work=A.S. Roma |date=5 July 2022 |language=en |archive-date=8 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220708095027/https://www.asroma.com/en/news/2022/7/zeki-celik-completes-move-to-roma |url-status=dead }}</ref> He made his [[Serie A]] debut in a 1–0 win over [[US Cremonese|Cremonese]] on 22 August 2022.

==International career==
Çelik made his professional debut for the [[Turkey national football team|Turkey national team]] in a 1–1 friendly with [[Russia national football team|Russia]] on 5 June 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=202&ftxtID=29439|title=RUSYA 1–1 TÜRKİYE – A Milli Takım Haber Detayları TFF|website=www.tff.org|access-date=5 June 2018|archive-date=28 December 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211228153330/https://www.tff.org/default.aspx?pageID=202&ftxtID=29439|url-status=live}}</ref>

